<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
<title>OG RATS — Whitepaper</title>

<style>
:root{
  --bg:#0b0b0f;
  --card:#141420;
  --text:#e5e7eb;
  --muted:#9ca3af;
  --accent:#3b82f6;
  --border:rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
}

*{
  margin:0;
  padding:0;
  box-sizing:border-box;
  font-family:system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, Arial;
}

body{
  background:var(--bg);
  color:var(--text);
  line-height:1.7;
}

header{
  position:sticky;
  top:0;
  background:rgba(11,11,15,0.7);
  backdrop-filter:blur(12px);
  border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);
  padding:14px 6%;
  display:flex;
  align-items:center;
  gap:12px;
}

header img{
  width:38px;
  height:38px;
  border-radius:10px;
}

header span{
  font-weight:700;
  letter-spacing:1px;
}

.container{
  max-width:900px;
  margin:auto;
  padding:30px 20px 80px;
}

.card{
  background:var(--card);
  border:1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius:16px;
  padding:22px;
  margin-bottom:14px;
}

h1,h2,h3{
  color:#93c5fd;
  margin-bottom:10px;
}

p{
  margin-bottom:10px;
}

ul,ol{
  padding-left:18px;
  margin-top:10px;
}

li{
  margin-bottom:6px;
}

.highlight{
  margin-top:10px;
  padding:10px 12px;
  border-left:3px solid var(--accent);
  background:rgba(59,130,246,0.08);
  border-radius:10px;
}

.footer-img{
  width:100%;
  border-radius:16px;
  margin-top:20px;
  border:1px solid var(--border);
}

footer{
  text-align:center;
  padding:40px 20px;
  color:var(--muted);
}

.buttons{
  display:flex;
  justify-content:center;
  gap:12px;
  flex-wrap:wrap;
  margin-top:18px;
}

.btn{
  display:flex;
  align-items:center;
  gap:8px;
  padding:12px 18px;
  border-radius:12px;
  text-decoration:none;
  font-weight:600;
  color:white;
  background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
  border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
  transition:0.2s;
}

.btn:hover{
  transform:translateY(-2px);
  border-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5);
}

.icon{
  width:18px;
  height:18px;
  fill:white;
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<header>
  <img src="logo.png" alt="OG RATS Logo">
  <span>OG RATS</span>
</header>

<div class="container">

<div class="card">
<h1>🐀 OG RATS — Whitepaper</h1>
</div>

<!-- 1 -->
<div class="card">
<h2>1. Introduction</h2>

<h3>1.1 What is OG RATS?</h3>

<p>OG RATS is a collection of 2,222 NFTs built on Ronin Network.</p>

<p>The project is focused on community, meme culture, social events, and active participation across Discord and X.</p>

<p>OG RATS aims to build an ecosystem driven by its holders through activity, creativity, and collaboration.</p>

<p>The project artwork is created by @NinjaRoninN.</p>

<h3>1.2 General Information</h3>

<p>Blockchain: Ronin Network</p>
<p>Standard: ERC-721</p>
<p>Supply: 2,222 NFTs</p>
<p>Mint: Free Mint</p>
<p>Focus: Community & Social Engagement</p>
</div>

<!-- 2 -->
<div class="card">
<h2>2. The OG RATS NFT</h2>

<h3>2.1 NFT Utility</h3>

<p>Holding an OG RATS grants access to:</p>

<p>private Discord community</p>
<p>weekly events</p>
<p>social activities</p>
<p>community rewards</p>
<p>access to the Relic system</p>
<p>future ecosystem activities</p>

<h3>2.2 Holder Philosophy</h3>

<p>OG RATS is built around active participation.</p>

<p>The ecosystem rewards:</p>

<p>social activity</p>
<p>creativity</p>
<p>community interaction</p>
<p>ongoing support for the project</p>

<p class="highlight">👉 The goal is not passive holding, but active participation within the community.</p>
</div>

<!-- 3 -->
<div class="card">
<h2>3. The OG RATS Ecosystem</h2>

<h3>3.1 How the Ecosystem Works</h3>

<ol>
<li>Hold OG RATS</li>
<li>Participate in events and activities</li>
<li>Create social activity and content</li>
<li>Earn rewards and Relic NFTs</li>
<li>Create unique 1/1 NFTs</li>
<li>Expand the Relic Collection</li>
<li>Strengthen the community ecosystem</li>
</ol>

<h3>3.2 Community Participation</h3>

<p>Community activity is the core of the project.</p>

<p>Valued contributions include:</p>

<p>Discord participation</p>
<p>activity on X</p>
<p>memes</p>
<p>creative content</p>
<p>ecosystem support</p>
<p>interaction with other Ronin communities</p>
</div>

<!-- 4 -->
<div class="card">
<h2>4. Events & Activities</h2>

<h3>4.1 Weekly Events</h3>

<p>OG RATS hosts between 1 and 2 events every week.</p>

<p>These events maintain consistent community activity.</p>

<h3>4.2 Event Types</h3>

<p>Events may include:</p>

<p>meme contests</p>
<p>creative challenges</p>
<p>X raids</p>
<p>social competitions</p>
<p>engagement activities</p>
<p>Discord events</p>
<p>collaborations</p>

<h3>4.3 Rewards</h3>

<p>Possible rewards include:</p>

<p>OG RATS NFTs</p>
<p>NFTs from Ronin projects</p>
<p>whitelist spots</p>
<p>special roles</p>
<p>collaboration access</p>
<p>Relic system access</p>
<p>Relic NFTs</p>

<p class="highlight">👉 Events are the main reward mechanism of the ecosystem.</p>
</div>

<!-- 5 -->
<div class="card">
<h2>5. The Relic System</h2>

<h3>5.1 What is a Relic?</h3>

<p>A Relic is a special NFT within the OG RATS ecosystem.</p>

<p>It functions as a redeemable access key that allows holders to create a unique 1/1 NFT inside the Relic Collection.</p>

<h3>5.2 How to Obtain a Relic</h3>

<p>Relic NFTs can be obtained through:</p>

<p>community events</p>
<p>contests</p>
<p>social participation</p>
<p>ecosystem activity</p>
<p>collaborations</p>
<p>optional support mint</p>

<h3>5.3 Optional Relic Mint</h3>

<p>Price: ~$10 USD</p>

<p>Designed for:</p>

<p>project supporters</p>
<p>collectors</p>
<p>direct access users</p>

<p>Important:</p>

<p>completely optional</p>
<p>no advantages in events</p>
<p>not required for participation</p>

<p class="highlight">👉 The purpose is to support project growth.</p>
</div>

<!-- 6 -->
<div class="card">
<h2>6. Creation of 1/1 NFTs</h2>

<h3>6.1 Redeeming Relics</h3>

<p>When a holder redeems a Relic NFT:</p>

<p>1. The Relic is consumed</p>
<p>2. The holder gains 1/1 creation rights</p>
<p>3. NFT can be created individually or with team</p>
<p>4. NFT is added to Relic Collection</p>

<h3>6.2 Creative Freedom</h3>

<p>Full freedom for creation is given to holders.</p>

<p>The goal is community-driven artistic expansion.</p>

<h3>6.3 Value</h3>

<p>Relics represent:</p>

<p>participation</p>
<p>creativity</p>
<p>community activity</p>
<p>exclusive access</p>

<p class="highlight">👉 Relics transform activity into art.</p>
</div>

<!-- 7 -->
<div class="card">
<h2>7. The Relic Collection</h2>

<h3>7.1 Overview</h3>

<p>Second official OG RATS collection composed of 1/1 NFTs.</p>

<h3>7.2 Rules</h3>

<p>Max supply: 1,000 NFTs</p>
<p>All 1/1 unique pieces</p>
<p>No pre-mint</p>
<p>Only via Relics</p>
<p>Organic growth</p>

<h3>7.3 Vision</h3>

<p>Focused on:</p>

<p>creativity</p>
<p>identity</p>
<p>collaboration</p>
<p>artistic value</p>

<p class="highlight">👉 Each NFT becomes part of OG RATS history.</p>
</div>

<!-- 8 -->
<div class="card">
<h2>8. Collaborations</h2>

<p>OG RATS may collaborate across Ronin Network.</p>

<p>Includes:</p>

<p>joint events</p>
<p>competitions</p>
<p>raids</p>
<p>shared rewards</p>
<p>partner NFTs</p>
<p>collaborative Relics</p>
</div>

<!-- 9 -->
<div class="card">
<h2>9. Future of the Project</h2>

<p>May evolve with:</p>

<p>new event formats</p>
<p>social mechanics</p>
<p>community systems</p>
<p>interaction tools</p>
<p>staking systems (future)</p>

<p class="highlight">👉 Growth depends on community feedback.</p>
</div>

<!-- 10 -->
<div class="card">
<h2>10. Philosophy</h2>

<p>Not a financial product.</p>

<p>No profit guarantees.</p>

<p>Value comes from:</p>

<p>participation</p>
<p>creativity</p>
<p>culture</p>
<p>social engagement</p>
<p>NFT creation</p>
</div>

<!-- 11 -->
<div class="card">
<h2>11. Closing</h2>

<p>OG RATS is a living community built by holders.</p>

<p>Every event and Relic NFT contributes to ecosystem growth.</p>

<p>The Relic Collection is a permanent archive of creativity on Ronin Network.</p>
</div>

